ZH: 我们都应该遵守诺言。
EN: We should all keep our promises.

ZH: 我向他做出了诺言，我会帮他度过难关。
EN: I made a promise to him that I would help him get through tough times.

ZH: 不要轻易许下诺言，除非你能够兑现。
EN: Don't make promises lightly unless you can keep them.

ZH: 他从来不会食言，总是兑现自己的诺言。
EN: He never breaks his promises and always keeps his word.

ZH: 诺言是构建信任的基石。
EN: Promises are the foundation of trust.

ZH: 她说了一些诺言，却从未实现过。
EN: She made some promises but never fulfilled them.

ZH: 这个国家遵守诺言，与其他国家和平共处。
EN: This country keeps its promises and lives in peace with other countries.

ZH: 他的诺言给我们带来了希望。
EN: His promises bring hope to us.

ZH: 有些诺言比黄金更珍贵。
EN: Some promises are more precious than gold.

ZH: 我发誓会守护她，这不只是一个诺言。
EN: I swear to protect her, this is not just a promise.

ZH: 如果你不能履行诺言，就不要轻易承诺。
EN: If you cannot keep your promises, do not make them lightly.

ZH: 对于友谊而言，诺言至关重要。
EN: Promises are crucial for friendship.

ZH: 他的诺言如阳光一样温暖。
EN: His promises are as warm as sunshine.

ZH: 让我们共同守护这个诺言。
EN: Let's keep this promise together.

ZH: 诺言可以是一种力量。
EN: Promises can be a source of strength.

ZH: 过去一直追随着这个诺言。
EN: I have been following this promise all along.

ZH: 他的诺言给了我们勇气。
EN: His promises give us courage.

ZH: 珍惜诺言，尊重承诺。
EN: Cherish promises and respect commitments.

ZH: 我们必须信守自己的诺言。
EN: We must keep our promises.

ZH: 诺言如同一束光明，照亮前行的路。
EN: Promises are like a beam of light, illuminating the path ahead.
